cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on human-robot interaction and navigation in an indoor environment. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the dataset includes eye gaze data and sensor data collected by a 3D lidar. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes metrics to analyze motion trajectory datasets. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the importance of understanding human behavior for robots and intelligent systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also relevant as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to enable systems to perceive, track, learn and predict human behavior.
